body.body: Safety Recall Action Notice 553 - R41 DATA LABEL (Australian Stationary Noise Label)
Subject: R41 DATA LABEL (Australian Stationary Noise Label)
Internal investigations have identified that the R41 DATA LABEL (Australian Stationary Noise Label) does not contain all the necessary information.
Dealers are required to install a new R41 DATA LABEL as described in the procedures below.
STOP DELIVERY OF AFFECTED MOTORCYCLES IMMEDIATELY.

DO NOT deliver a motorcycle affected by this Safety Recall Action Notice to a customer until you have completed, or confirmed completion of, the procedures described in this Safety Recall Action Notice.
Delivering a motorcycle subject to an outstanding Safety Recall Action Notice may contravene local or national laws in your market, territory or country.

Triumph Australia must instigate a Safety Recall Action in their country in accordance with the national recall code of practice. For vehicles in dealer stock, the safety recall MUST be actioned before delivery to the customer.
Dealers are to prioritise repair of customer owned motorcycles before any unsold motorcycles.
Models listed in the VIN ranges above.
Service Bulletin - Note - Identification of Affected Motorcycles
Some affected motorcycles listed in the VIN range will have been modified and repaired by Triumph prior to their release from the factory.
Unmodified motorcycles can be identified by checking the ‘VIN Enquiry’ on www.triumphonline.net.
T3930605 - Parts Kit - R41 DATA LABEL, Kit
2 x T3331044 Screw, Pan/HD, TX,M6x1.0x16, ENC
Once completed, please mark the Service Record Book that the requirements of this bulletin have been complied with.

Before returning the motorcycle to the customer, download the latest calibration to the engine electronic control module, chassis electronic control module (if fitted) and instruments (if applicable) using the current version of the Triumph diagnostic software.
Dealers using Triumph Warranty On-Line with Parts Auto Ordering Flag switched on:

Order all repair parts by submitting a New Prior through the Warranty On-Line system. Entering the above repair code in a New Prior will automatically add the parts required and labour times for this Service Bulletin.
Service Bulletin - Genuine Parts Return Instructions - Not Applicable
Install the new R41 DATA LABEL (Australian Stationary Noise Label) following the procedure listed below.
Make sure the motorcycle is stabilised and adequately supported.
A correctly supported motorcycle will help prevent it from falling.
An unstable motorcycle may fall, causing injury to the operator or damage to the motorcycle.

The stationary noise label (R41 Data Label) is supplied with the stationary noise information of the motorcycle to which it relates. Ensure part number on the R41 Data Label backing paper matches the part number listed in the Genuine Parts Information table of this Service Bulletin.
Once the label has been applied, it cannot be removed without irreparable damage.
Location of the R41 Data Label on the Motorcycle
For location and access to the R41 Data Label refer to
Installation of the R41 Data Label
The surface to which the label is affixed must be clean and dry to ensure that the adhesive has a sound base to adhere to. Use a cleaning wipe for this purpose.
Two of the labels in the label set are blank. Only the R41 Data Label will have text on it.
Carefully cut the R41 Data Label from the label set. Ensure there is enough backing paper around its edge, as shown in the illustration below.
Partially roll back the backing paper to expose the adhesive at the top of the label.
Carefully align the top edge of the new label with the top edge of the original label.
Once the label edge is aligned, accurately affix the top part of the label and gradually pull away the backing paper then gently affix the rest of the label.
Once the whole label is accurately affixed, firmly rub down to remove any air bubbles.
